readValues

public void readValues(Input input)
                throws IOException
read the value based on type If the size of the value is greater than 4 bytes read the value directly from the valueOffset field (pointed to by the savedValueOffset). Else read the value from where the valueOffset points to. Each value can be of a different type which is stored in a different object. Based on the tag's type and if the value is an array or not, it will be stored in the appropriate object.

Parameters:
input -
Throws:
IOException
